Introduction¶

Ford GoBike is a regional public bicycle sharing system in the San Francisco Bay Area, California.

The bikes can be unlocked from one station and returned to any other station in the system, making them ideal for one-way trips. Clients can use bike share system to commute to work or school, get to appointments or social engagements and more.

The following data summary will focus on various aspects of the Ford Gobike system in 2019. I hope to summarize different aspects of data to help this shared bicycle system better understand customer needs and optimize the physical system.

Main features of interest¶

I am very interested in the usage habits of the client groups of the Ford Gobike system. These habits include the way of use, purpose of use and time of use, etc. These features can help Gobike group to make better business decisions such as which day of the week should provide more bikes.

I am also interested in investigate the average traveling distance for each user type. This can help the team estimate the bike repair time. Regularly checking the safety of the bicycle is a prerequisite for better service.

I will also test the rental method for clients. By understanding the way they like to rent bicycles, it can help the Gobike team build a better cooperative relationship with the rental platform. This is a win-win situation.

Define (4) : Create column 'distance'¶

Code :¶

Useful link: https://www.pythonprogramming.in/basic-python-programs/calculate-distance-between-two-points-on-earth.html#:~:text=Calculate%20distance%20between%20two%20points%20on%20Earth.%20Write,%2B%20cos%28t1%29%20%C3%97%20cos%28t2%29%20%C3%97%20cos%28g1%20%E2%88%92%20g2%29%29

In [32]:
# Create distances
from math import sin, cos, sqrt, atan2, radians


def distances (lat_1,long_1,lat_2,long_2):
    R = 6371.01
    lat_1 = radians(lat_1)
    long_1 = radians(long_1)
    lat_2 = radians(lat_2)
    long_2 = radians(long_2)
    dis_lon = long_2 - long_1
    dis_lat = lat_2 - lat_1

    a = sin(dis_lat / 2)**2 + cos(lat_1) * cos(lat_2) * sin(dis_lon / 2)**2
    b = 2 * atan2(sqrt(a), sqrt(1 - a))

    distance = R * b
    return np.float64(round(1000*distance))

df_clean['distance'] = df_clean.apply(lambda row: distances(row['start_station_latitude'], row['start_station_longitude'], row['end_station_latitude'], row['end_station_longitude']), axis=1)

Dataset Structure¶

  • The data was collected from January 2019 to December 2019.

  • There were approximately 2,507,000 bike rides in the San Francisco Bay area of California, USA.

  • I only left nine columns of data in the original database

  • To summarize the data better, I added 12 additional columns

Bivariate Exploration Summary¶

  • Subscriber is the main target audiences who rent bikes in each month and reach its peak in March. Subscribers use Gobike system more often during weekdays than weekends and they rent bikes more often around commute hours (8-9am and 5-6pm).

  • 90% of the clients who rent bikes through the app.

  • July has the highest number of GoBike trips.

  • Number of GoBike trips for subscriber is around 5 time as its for customers.

  • More tourists choose to come for vacation in the second half of the year. GoBike customer's usage reaching its peak in December.

  • In December, subscribers demand for bicycles was significantly reduced by half.

  • Application rentals in July can reach 70% of a yearly rental. It can be seen that the number of trips in July should be higher than in other months.

  • Only a few users choose to share bicycles with others. Bike sharing occurred more often in the first quarter.

Multivariate Exploration Summary¶

  • Bike share ONLY happens on Subscribers. Although only a small percentage of people choose to share bicycles, these people prefer to share bicycles with others in the first quarter.

  • The trend is quite different for subscriber and customer. There is NO customers using bike sharing system. It might because customers only use Ford GoBike system for tourists. They return the bike once arrive their distination. As for subscribers, there are part of the subcribers choose bike sharing in each month, especially in March.

  • Both subscribers and customers usually choose to travel relatively far in the fourth quarter. To be more precise, travel distances are generally longer in November. This may be because the company will have more business trips at the end of the year, and travelers choose to take a vacation after finishing a year of planning.

Summary¶

Ford GoBike System is an innovative project, which provides bike-renting service for moving around in the city, both for work and travel.

There are two types of users: Subscribers and Customers.

There are two rental methods: App and Clipper.

Subscribers (80.6%) are primarily using GoBike system for daily commute. (Short distance traveling)

Customers (19.4%) are usually tourists who use the GoBike system to explore the Bay Area.

App: 90% of the clients prefer to rent bikes through the app.

Average traveling distance: Travel distances are generally longer in November. This may due to more business trips at the end of the year, and travelers choose to take a vacation after finishing a year of planning.
